# PM-Brain: Private Mode
# ================================
# This template configures the repo for PRIVATE use - ideal for:
# - Personal learning only
# - Company-specific work
# - Confidential information
#
# What's ignored (not tracked):
# - Daily learning logs (`00-Meta/1-daily-log-*.md`)
# - Weekly/monthly reflections (`00-Meta/0.1-Learning-Log/*/`)
# - Growth portfolio entries (`00-Meta/0.2-Growth-Portfolio/*.md`)
# - Self-assessments (`00-Meta/self-assessment-*.md`)
# - Company context and stakeholder info
# - Active initiatives and research
#
# What's tracked:
# - Templates and frameworks
# - Documentation and guides
# - Shared learning resources
#
# To activate this mode:
#   cat .gitignore.private >> .gitignore
#   git add .gitignore
#   git commit -m "setup: Switch to private mode"

# ============================================
# Personal Product Sense Content
# ============================================

# Daily logs (your private practice)
00-Meta/1-daily-log-*.md

